    • AbstractTypedGenerator

      protected AbstractTypedGenerator()
      Crates a new instance.

      Infers generated values type from the generic type arguments of this instance class. The class must extend AbstractTypedGenerator specifying the generic types.

      Example: 

       class MyGenerator
 extends AbstractTypedGenerator<MyValues> {
     ...
 }

    • nullableRandomValue

      public T nullableRandomValue()
      Returns a random value of the supported type allowing null values.

      The returned value has a probability of be null except for native types. If not null behaves as randomValue().

      Specified by:
